NSW, Hunter Valley:
951 Bylong Valley Way Baerami &
1142 Hermitage Road Pokolbin

• Outstanding integrated vineyard, winery and cellar door located within the renowned and highly regarded Hunter Valley region comprising;

- Baerami 575 Ha (vineyard, winery, cellar door)
- Pokolbin 44 HA (winery, cellar door)
• 86 HA planted to various varieties including Shiraz, Merlot, Cabernet Sauvignon, Cabernet Franc, Petit Verdot, Pinot Noir, Chardonnay, Verdelho and Semillon varieties
• Average annual production of 500 to 900 tonnes per annum
• Winery capacity of 2,500 tonnes (Baerami)
• Pokolbin winery currently leased for $80,000 per annum (approx.)
• Extensive Goulburn River water resources totalling 777 ML
• High quality plant and equipment available
• Numerous structural improvements
• Scope for expansion in all facets of the current operation
• Available in one line or separately


“Excellent winery able to provide wines of high to very high quality, knocking on the door of 5-star rating.” – James Halliday, Author of James Halliday Australian Wine Companion 2013

Under instruction from Neil Cussen and Vaughan Strawbridge in their capacity as Receivers and Managers

AUSTRALIA'S FINEST LUXURY ESTATE - SOLD

The Tower Estate Lodge and Tower Estate Winery have been sold.

Located in the heart of the Hunter Valley, Tower Estate enjoys
the reputation as Australia's finest luxury estate.

Tower Lodge & Tower Estate Winery

* Tower Lodge - 12 luxuriously appointed suites
* Tower Estate Winery - 5 star James Halliday rated, with 300 tonne* capacity
* Ability to leverage off strong reputation
* Prime freehold 16Ha* landholding, both assets on same title

PEPPERS CONVENT:
-  One of a kind boutique hotel comprising 17 guest rooms
-  Operational improvement and repositioning
-  Stunning tree-lined drive to circular entry
-  Restaurant Eighty Eight
-  Conference room with seating for up to 20 guests
-  Detached purpose-built Grand Marquee
-  Pool and tennis court
-  2.933 hectares over two titles

CIRCA 1876:
-  One of the most iconic and recognisable fine dining restaurants in the Hunter Valley, typifying the best of the modern Australian dining experience
-  Ranked in Australia's top 500 restaurants, scoring 1 Chef Hat
-  2 buildings - original heritage ironbark cottage (restored and renovated), and larger main dining building which seats 120 guests
-  Extensive commercial kitchen and onsite kitchen garden
-  The chapel
-  1.9945 hectares over two titles

For Sale by Expressions of Interest, closing Thursday 16th June 2016.
